`‖septic_d7_P3_C3_quad_poly(a,b)‖ ≤ (2144/55296) · (‖a‖+‖b‖)⁷`.

67 explicit deg-7 terms, max |numerator| = 32, LCM = 55296.
Per-term uniform bound `(32/55296) · s^7` summed over Fin 67. -/
theorem norm_septic_d7_P3_C3_quad_poly_le (a b : 𝔸) :
    ‖septic_d7_P3_C3_quad_poly 𝕂 a b‖ ≤ (2144 / 55296 : ℝ) * (‖a‖ + ‖b‖) ^ 7 := by
  set s := ‖a‖ + ‖b‖ with hs_def
  have hs_nn : 0 ≤ s := by positivity
  have ha_le : ‖a‖ ≤ s := by linarith [norm_nonneg b]
  have hb_le : ‖b‖ ≤ s := by linarith [norm_nonneg a]
  rw [septic_d7_P3_C3_quad_poly_eq_sum]
  calc ‖∑ i : Fin 67, SepticD7P3C3QuadTerm (𝕂 := 𝕂) a b i‖
      ≤ ∑ i : Fin 67, ‖SepticD7P3C3QuadTerm (𝕂 := 𝕂) a b i‖ := norm_sum_le _ _
    _ ≤ ∑ _i : Fin 67, (32 / 55296 : ℝ) * s^7 :=
        Finset.sum_le_sum (fun i _ => SepticD7P3C3QuadTerm_norm_le (𝕂 := 𝕂) a b s ha_le hb_le hs_nn i)
    _ = 67 * ((32 / 55296 : ℝ) * s^7) := by
        rw [Finset.sum_const, Finset.card_univ, Fintype.card_fin]; ring
    _ = (2144 / 55296 : ℝ) * s^7 := by ring



/-! ## 9-piece operator-form decomposition of septic_d8_perturbation_poly

From CAS verification (`scripts/verify_d8_operator_decomp.py`):

    septic_d8_perturbation_poly
      = septic_d8_P2_poly + septic_d8_P3_poly + septic_d8_P4_poly
        + septic_d8_P5_poly + septic_d8_P6_poly
        + septic_d8_cross_V2_V3_poly + septic_d8_cross_V2_V4_poly
        + septic_d8_cross_V2_V5_poly + septic_d8_cross_V3_V4_poly

Each piece corresponds to a specific operator-form perturbation:
  • P_j := (bch(x + V_j, ½a) − bch(x, ½a))_deg8  (single-V_j perturbation).
  • Cross(V_j, V_k) := (bch(x+V_j+V_k, ½a) − bch(x+V_j, ½a)
                       − bch(x+V_k, ½a) + bch(x, ½a))_deg8  (mixed cross).

d8 analog of the 6-piece d7 decomposition. Three potential cross pieces
(Cross(V_2,V_6), Cross(V_3,V_5), Cross(V_4,V_5)) vanish at deg 8 because
the required C_p with p+(j-1)+(k-1) = 8 and j,k ≥ 3 forces p ≤ 2, but
C_2 has only 1 z-position and cannot admit bilinear substitution.

Foundation for the Phase C-septic operator-form identity (eventual O(s⁹)
joint bound replacing the current O(s⁸) per-piece bound on
septic_d8_perturbation_poly via Lipschitz bounds on each operator form).
-/

