P_2_d8 = (bch(x + V_2, ½a) - bch(x, ½a))_deg8 splits into 3 sub-pieces.
At deg 8 with V_2 = (1/2)·[½a, b] (deg 2), the contributions come from
C_p substitutions with k V_2's such that p + k = 8 and k ≤ #z-positions in C_p:
