  • C_6 quadratic-in-V_2 (k=2, p=6): bch_sextic_term(x+V_2, a') - bch_sextic_term(x, a') at deg 8.
  • C_5 cubic-in-V_2 (k=3, p=5): bch_quintic_term(x+V_2, a') - bch_quintic_term(x, a') at deg 8.

Higher k impossible: C_p with p ≤ 4 has ≤ 2 z-positions, can't accept k ≥ 4 substitutions.

d8 analog of `septic_d7_P2_pieces_decomp` (d7 has only 2 sub-pieces:
C_5 quad + C_6 lin, since cubic-in-V_2 at d7 requires p+3=7 → p=4 with 3 z-positions,
